instructions:
Write an async function `safeParseJSON(jsonString)` that tries to parse a JSON string. If parsing succeeds, return the parsed object. If it fails, return null instead of throwing an error.

Example: safeParseJSON('{"name":"John"}') returns { name: 'John' }
Example: safeParseJSON('invalid json') returns null

starterCode:
async function safeParseJSON(jsonString) {
  // Your code here

}

solution:
async function safeParseJSON(jsonString) {
  try {
    return JSON.parse(jsonString);
  } catch (error) {
    return null;
  }
}
